fields.output_description:
Returns a JSON object (PUG View) with top-level key "Record". Example (abridged):
{
  "Record": {
    "RecordType": "CID",
    "RecordNumber": 2244,
    "RecordTitle": "Aspirin",
    "Section": [
      {
        "TOCHeading": "Patents",
        "Description": "Patent applications/documents that mention this compound.",
        "DisplayControls": {"ListType": "Columns"},
        "Information": [
          {
            "ReferenceNumber": 35,
            "Value": {
              "StringWithMarkup": [
                {"String": "US5972916", "Markup": [{"Start": 0, "Length": 9, "URL": "https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/patent/US5972916"}]},
                {"String": "US6015577", "Markup": [{"Start": 0, "Length": 9, "URL": "https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/patent/US6015577"}]},
                ... (additional patent IDs)
              ]
            }
          }
        ],
        "Section": [
          {"TOCHeading": "Depositor-Supplied Patent Identifiers", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "WIPO PATENTSCOPE", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "FDA Orange Book Patents", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "Chemical Co-Occurrences in Patents", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "Chemical-Disease Co-Occurrences in Patents", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "Chemical-Gene Co-Occurrences in Patents", "Information": [...]},
          {"TOCHeading": "Chemical-Organism Co-Occurrences in Patents", "Information": [...]}
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Reference": [ {"ReferenceNumber": 35, "SourceName": "DrugBank", ...}, ... ]
  }
}
Key points:
- Record.Section[0] (TOCHeading "Patents") holds patent ID list in Information[0].Value.StringWithMarkup (each element has String patent identifier and Markup[0].URL link).
- Nested Section array contains related subsections (e.g., WIPO, FDA Orange Book, co-occurrence panels) each with its own Information entries.
- Co-occurrence panels often provide structured headers or external table references (e.g., ExternalTableName or StringWithMarkup rows) for downstream follow-up queries.
- Reference array cites data sources (DrugBank, FDA, PubChem, WIPO, etc.).
LLM can extract patent identifiers by iterating Record.Section[0].Information[0].Value.StringWithMarkup[*].String and their URLs from Markup[*].URL.

Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "PropertyTable": {
    "Properties": [
      {
        "CID": 2244,
        "MolecularWeight": 180.157,
        "IUPACName": "2-acetyloxybenzoic acid",
        "CanonicalSMILES": "CC(=O)OC1=CC=CC=C1C(=O)O",
        ...
      }
    ]
  }
}

Where:
- PropertyTable.Properties list: each element contains properties for that CID;
- Property names determined by {property_list}, example here is ["MolecularWeight","IUPACName","CanonicalSMILES"].
After calling, LLM can directly access these important molecular properties for subsequent chemical/pharmacological reasoning.

Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "IdentifierList": {
    "CID": [2244, 11394, ...]
  }
}

Where:
- IdentifierList.CID list: all CIDs matching the name. Usually the first one is the most common compound ID.
After calling, LLM can obtain the PubChem ID list corresponding to the input chemical name, for further property or structure queries by CID.

Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "IdentifierList": {
    "CID": [2244]
  }
}

Where: CID array contains all compound IDs that exactly match this SMILES. LLM can use this tool to map structure to CID.

Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "IdentifierList": {
    "CID": [241, 1188, ...]
  }
}

Where: CID array contains all compound IDs in PubChem database that contain this substructure. LLM can use this to understand which molecules contain this group.

fields.input_description:
Input is:
- smiles: SMILES for similarity comparison;
- threshold: specify similarity threshold, PubChem will return all CIDs with similarity ≥ threshold.

fields.output_description:
Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "IdentifierList": {
    "CID": [2244, 2245, ...]
  }
}

Where: CID array contains compound IDs with similarity above specified threshold to target molecule. LLM can use this for chemical similarity analysis.

fields.input_description:
Input is:
- cid: compound ID;
- image_size: desired image pixel size, format is "widthxheight" (e.g., "150x150").

fields.output_description:
Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "InformationList": {
    "Information": [
      {
        "CID": 2244,
        "Synonym": ["Aspirin", "Acetylsalicylic acid", ...]
      }
    ]
  }
}

Where: InformationList.Information[0].Synonym is a string list containing all synonyms. LLM can use this to identify various chemical nomenclature.

fields.input_description:
Input is:
- cid: compound ID;
- xref_types: list of external database types to query.

fields.output_description:
Returns a JSON object with structure example:
{
  "InformationList": {
    "Information": [
      {
        "CID": 2244,
        "XRef": {
          "ChEBI": "CHEBI:15365",
          "DrugBank": "DB00945",
          "KEGG": "D00134",
          ...
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}

Where: In XRef dictionary, keys are external resource names, values are corresponding resource IDs. LLM can use this for cross-database linking and knowledge integration.
